results.name: Number of partitions of n into parts 6k+2 and 6k+5 with at least one part of each type.
link: Alois P. Heinz, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..5000 (first 100 terms from Robert Price)
mathematica: nmax = 68; s1 = Range[0, nmax/6]*6 + 2; s2 = Range[0, nmax/6]*6 + 5;
x_ /; ContainsAny[x, s1 ] && ContainsAny[x, s2 ]], {n, 1, nmax}] (* _Robert Price_, Aug 13 2020 *)
nmax = 68; l = Rest@CoefficientList[Series[(-1 + 1/Product[(1 - x^(6 k + 2)), {k, 0, nmax}])*(-1 + 1/Product[(1 - x^(6 k + 5)), {k, 0, nmax}]), {x, 0, nmax}], x]  (* _Robert Price_, Aug 16 2020 *)
